# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Jameye waitlist → Google Forms
#
# Copy this file to ".env" (already gitignored) and fill in the values below.
# Every var MUST start with PUBLIC_ — Astro/Vite only exposes PUBLIC_* to the
# browser, and the waitlist modal runs client-side.
#
# The modal collects: Name (required), Email (required),
# Nickname (optional — auto-generated from the name if blank),
# Referred by (optional — meant to be someone else's nickname).
#
# Before submitting it checks the published responses sheet and rejects a
# signup if the EMAIL or NICKNAME is already taken (Name and Referred-by may
# repeat). If the responses CSV is unset or unreachable, the check is skipped
# (fails open) so signups are never blocked.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── 1. The Google Form ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a Google Form with these short-answer questions:
#   Name · Nickname · Email · Referred by · Avatar
# (Avatar stores the chosen option id: avatar_1 … avatar_4.)
#
# Open the form, click ⋮ (top-right) → "Get pre-filled link", fill each field
# with a dummy value, then "Get link". The copied URL looks like:
#
#   https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx/viewform?usp=pp_url
#       &entry.1111111111=Name
#       &entry.2222222222=Email
#       &entry.3333333333=Nickname
#       &entry.4444444444=Referred
#
# • FORM_ID  = the "1FAIpQLS…" segment (between /d/e/ and /viewform).
# • ENTRY_*  = the "entry.NNNNNNNNNN" key that precedes each dummy value.
#              (Include the literal "entry." prefix.)

PUBLIC_WAITLIST_FORM_ID=1FAIpQLSxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_ENTRY_NAME=entry.1111111111
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_ENTRY_EMAIL=entry.2222222222
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_ENTRY_NICKNAME=entry.3333333333
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_ENTRY_REFERRED=entry.4444444444
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_ENTRY_AVATAR=entry.5555555555


# ── 2. The responses sheet (for uniqueness checks) ───────────────────────────
# In the Form: Responses tab → "Link to Sheets" to create the responses sheet.
# In that Sheet: File → Share → "Publish to web" → select the responses tab →
# format "Comma-separated values (.csv)" → Publish. Paste the resulting URL,
# which looks like:
#
#   https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-xxxxxxxx/pub?output=csv
#
# (Leave blank to disable the uniqueness check entirely.)

PUBLIC_WAITLIST_RESPONSES_CSV=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-xxxxxxxx/pub?output=csv

# Header text of the Email / Nickname columns in that sheet — i.e. the exact
# question titles. Match casing is ignored. Defaults shown below.
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_CSV_EMAIL_COL=Email
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_CSV_NICKNAME_COL=Nickname

# Columns used by the /leaderboard page (referral points + weekly movement).
# Defaults match the form's question titles; override only if yours differ.
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_CSV_REFERRED_COL=Referred by
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_CSV_TIMESTAMP_COL=Timestamp
PUBLIC_WAITLIST_CSV_AVATAR_COL=Avatar
